<%- include('partials/header', { 
  title: 'The Western Provinces',
  extraCss: 'world.css',
  extraHead: `
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/1.9.4/leaflet.min.css" />
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/leaflet/1.9.4/leaflet.min.js"></script>
  `
}) %>

<section>
  <h1>The Western Provinces</h1>
  <p>
    The Western Provinces are a vast, fractured region on the edge of the
    former Allyrian Empire. For centuries, the land was connected by roads,
    cities, and shared rule, but that ended after two long winters devastated
    the population and forced the empire to withdraw.
  </p>
  <p>
    Today, the Provinces are made up of hundreds of independent city-states —
    large cities, fortified towns, and smaller strongholds. They trade, fight,
    and form alliances, but nothing lasts long. Most people are either Salian
    or Caernic, though the difference between them is small and often mixed.
    Outside the settlements, much of the land has fallen into ruin or
    wilderness, and travel is always uncertain.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="map-box">
  <button id="fs-btn" title="Fullscreen">⛶</button>
  <div id="map"></div>
</section>

<aside id="info-overlay">
  <article id="info">
    <button id="info-close">✕</button>
    <h3 id="info-name">—</h3>
    <p id="info-desc"></p>
    <section id="info-body"></section>
    <footer id="info-coords"></footer>
  </article>
</aside>

<section id="controls">
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" id="hex-toggle" checked /> Show hex grid
  </label>
  <label>
    <input type="checkbox" id="labels-toggle" checked /> Show labels
  </label>
  <output id="coords">lat: — lng: —</output>
</section>

<script src="/js/world.js"></script>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>